        <td style="width:367px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">Congruent Triangles</text> are the same size, shape. To move one over another triangle, you can rotate them about an axis perpendicular to the Plane.</para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Equal internal angles </li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Equal side-lengths</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box">Each angle is in the same direction.</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> and <image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> are Congruent.</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> and <image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> are the same shape but not Congruent.</li>
          </list>
